From: D-Central Technologies <firmware@d-central.tech>
Subject: [PATCH] Disable getrandom() to avoid blocking during early boot

On the Zynq 7010, the entropy pool is not initialized fast enough
during early boot, causing dropbear to block indefinitely on
getrandom() syscall. This patch removes the getrandom() call and
falls back to /dev/urandom, which is sufficient for a research
firmware that runs on a private network.

This is NOT suitable for production firmware exposed to the internet.
For DCENTos production builds, we should instead seed entropy from
hardware sources (FPGA LFSR, ADC noise) during early init.

---
 src/dbrandom.c | 12 ------------
 1 file changed, 12 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/dbrandom.c b/src/dbrandom.c
index abcdef1..1234567 100644
--- a/src/dbrandom.c
+++ b/src/dbrandom.c
@@ -100,18 +100,6 @@ static int process_getrandom(void) {
-#ifdef HAVE_GETRANDOM
-static int process_getrandom() {
-	char buf[INIT_SEED_SIZE];
-	ssize_t ret;
-
-	ret = getrandom(buf, sizeof(buf), 0);
-	if (ret == sizeof(buf)) {
-		hash_state hs;
-		sha1_init(&hs);
-		sha1_process(&hs, buf, ret);
-		sha1_done(&hs, hashpool);
-		counter = 0;
-		return DROPBEAR_SUCCESS;
-	}
-	return DROPBEAR_FAILURE;
-}
-#endif
